n the breast and shoulders (almost exclusively for men) and the beard.<\/p>\n\n<p>It seems, that these hair bulbs have different sensibilities (number and expression of androgen receptors) so they react differently to androgen levels. This includes balding, pigmentation, growth and so on.<\/p>\n\n<p>These articles should be a good starting point, if you want to dive deeper into the topic:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23016593\" rel=\"nofollow\">Androgen actions on the human hair follicle: perspectives.<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10439260\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mechanism of action of androgen in human hair follicle.<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":16416,"question_id":16394,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16394/why-is-the-human-body-hair-not-uniformly-colored","last_activity_date":1396961598,"creation_date":1396886205,"answer_count":2,"title":"Why is the human body hair not uniformly colored?","body":"<p>Most of my body hair is black however my lip hair is light brown/blonde the rest of my beard region is black. Since hair color is genetic what causes this?<\/p>\n","question_id":16394,"tags":["genetics","epigenetics"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":190,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1396916973},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d9f9776938888dc91366dc6371544e91?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3258,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3258/stockfisch","reputation":87,"display_name":"Stockfisch","accept_rate":60},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/VmtoK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1320,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1320/alan-boyd","reputation":17240,"display_name":"Alan Boyd"},"score":0,"post_id":16344,"edited":false,"creation_date":1396638515,"comment_id":22040,"body":"But not including actual sea-going 