les of its use in that fashion:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connective_tissue\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connective_tissue<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.vetmed.vt.edu/education/curriculum/vm8054/Labs/Lab5/Lab5.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.vetmed.vt.edu/education/curriculum/vm8054/Labs/Lab5/Lab5.htm<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pitt.edu/~sshostak/biosci1450/hislec03.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.pitt.edu/~sshostak/biosci1450/hislec03.html<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":16399,"question_id":16398,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16398/what-is-this-abbreviation-ct-in-female-reproductive-system","last_activity_date":1396902785,"creation_date":1396901259,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is this abbreviation CT in female reproductive system","body":"<p>I have this sentence in my notes<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Ovary is surrounded by tunica albuginea and the cortex keeps the primordial follicles. The medulla containing CT and blood vessels develop from mesonephros. <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>I have these words in my mind about CT<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>tunica<\/li>\n<li>cyto- (maybe cytotrophoblast)<\/li>\n<li>corona (no other than corona radiata so not)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p><strong>What can CT be here?<\/strong><\/p>\n","question_id":16398,"tags":["human-biology","homework","embryology"],"score":0,"accepted_answer_id":16399,"down_vote_count":1,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":true,"view_count":81,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/77d74e56a5dbcc49b4cf214be37df5b8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6095,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6095/biology-lover","reputation":26,"display_name":"Biology Lover"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/VmtoK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1320,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1320/alan-boyd","