.com/avatar/c625f09c24ee8c9c270caa33cfd4ce7f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4579,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4579/har-wradim","reputation":2433,"display_name":"har-wradim"},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1396782155,"creation_date":1396782155,"body":"<p>An addition to the answer by Chris.<\/p>\n\n<p>Probably the most dangerous tapeworms for humans are <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Echinococcus\" rel=\"nofollow\">Echinococcus<\/a>. In humans they form cysts (in a variety of organs including brain) [it's because humans are \"interpreted\" as intermediate hosts], which can become very large and can cause death when untreated or disrupted.<\/p>\n","answer_id":16370,"question_id":16343,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16343/tapeworms-and-their-effect-on-humans","last_activity_date":1396782155,"creation_date":1396628943,"answer_count":2,"title":"Tapeworms and their effect on humans","body":"<p>I've read that some people in some countries actually use tapeworms as a form of losing weight.  What are the dangers to these people?<\/p>\n","question_id":16343,"tags":["parasitology"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":16346,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":62,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/97c181541960937621a547a4287d0362?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6258,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6258/brannon","reputation":106,"display_name":"Brannon"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":16357,"edited":false,"creation_date":1396722638,"comment_id":22061,"body":"Why do you want to change the cell m