ely share their genetic data<\/a> creating a market which can <a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/technology/archive/2012/05/the-perfect-milk-machine-how-big-data-transformed-the-dairy-industry/256423/\" rel=\"nofollow\">predict the value of a bull<\/a>.  The market for bull semen can be worth hundreds of dollars per impregnation. <\/p>\n\n<p>Why are bulls valued at such a greater rate than cows?  Because semen can be preserved, transported and used thousands of times while a cow can only calf one at a time.<\/p>\n","answer_id":16356,"question_id":16353,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16353/list-of-the-biggest-companies-that-work-in-selective-breeding","last_activity_date":1396708918,"creation_date":1396705145,"answer_count":1,"title":"List of the biggest companies that work in selective breeding","body":"<p>Looking at <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16330/book-recommendation-on-selective-breeding\">this question<\/a>, I've been wondering, What are the biggest private companies which work in both animal and non-animal selective breeding?<\/p>\n\n<p>Let me know if Biology.SE is not appropriate for this kind of question.<\/p>\n\n<p>Thank you<\/p>\n","question_id":16353,"tags":["evolution","zoology","natural-selection"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":248,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/89bd8263f33f9185b51c408666f6ee47?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6257,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6257/cppcoder","reputation":116,"display_name":"cppcoder"},"closed_date":1396710698,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16355/why-do-we-yawn-seeing-others-yawn","last_activity_date":1396708038,"creation_date":1396708038,"answer_count":0,"title":"Why do we yawn seeing others yawn","body":"<p>If I see another person yawning, I definitely feel to yawn.<br>\nWhy is that so?  <\/p>\n\n<p>What are the 