 where it elutes.<\/p>\n\n<p>Is it possible to compare the molecular weight of DNA and where it elutes to the molecular weight of proteins and peptides and where that elutes?<\/p>\n","question_id":16313,"tags":["dna","purification","chromatography"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":16347,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":200,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Kyg92.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6061,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6061/rhill45","reputation":2493,"display_name":"rhill45","accept_rate":79},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":16340,"edited":false,"creation_date":1407245562,"comment_id":30339,"body":"Which possibilities do you have for the extraction? Would this be more &quot;lab-like&quot; or more &quot;DIY-bio&quot;-style?"}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/16340/condensed-protocol-for-sequencing-a-portion-of-human-dna-from-buccal-sample","last_activity_date":1396624345,"creation_date":1396624345,"answer_count":0,"title":"condensed protocol for sequencing a portion of human DNA from buccal sample","body":"<p>Anyone have a short &amp; sweet protocol for PCR amplifying a region of human DNA (chromosomal or mt, I don't care) extracted from a buccal sample: including validated primer sequences and preferred method of DNA isolation from a buccal swab. I'm looking for a new exercise to run in my classroom. We would be able to follow the amplification up with Sanger sequencing, done in-house.  <\/p>\n","question_id":16340,"tags":["dna","dna-sequencing","pcr","human-genome"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":32,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.i